  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>A vial of thoroughly filtered Laublub oil, pale and clear. Safe for Delta Kilo Autarchs to consume as lubricant.</p><h2>Drink</h2><p>Target a creature and choose how many charges to feed it (Consumption Scaling). Each charge consumed restores 1 hour to the target's fluid gauge, up to the 48-hour cap.</p><h2>Douse</h2><p>Pour charges onto the ground to coat the area with oil (radius scales with charges spent: 1 charge = 2.5 ft radius, 2 = 3.75 ft, 3 = 5 ft). Any creature entering or starting its turn there must succeed on a DC 10 + the douser's Dexterity modifier Dexterity saving throw or fall prone (and take 1d8 fire damage if the oil has been ignited; standing up requires the same save). The oil evaporates after 1 minute. Igniting is GM adjudicated and grants a one-time +4 bonus to the triggering fire damage.</p><h2>Throw</h2><p>Ranged attack roll against a creature or object. On a hit, the target is coated in oil for 48 rounds. At the start of its turn, the target may spend its action and succeed on a DC 10 Dexterity saving throw to reduce the remaining duration by 5 rounds. Igniting (GM adjudicated) grants a one-time +4 bonus to the triggering fire damage; the oil then continues burning until the end of the target's next turn, dealing an additional 1d8 fire damage at the start of that turn (use the Continued Burn Damage activity).</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
